args: (But why do I wanna get stronger...?)
(For as long as I can remember, I wanted\nto be the strongest tomato around.)
(But what happens once I do it?)
(I ain't exactly an egghead in the ol' brains\ndepartment, so I'll be knock-kneed if I got\nany idea about that one...)
Aw, saltmuffins! I got no clue!\nNo clue, I tells ya!
Er, apologies for my outburst, Yachiyo.\nYou just surprised me when you shouted.
Well, crumbs. Sorry about that. Me and the\nol' noggin here were just doing some\nheavy lifting. Anyway, you need me?
Yes. You recall the little girl we saved\nfrom the Mukuroshu?
We received a letter from her family\nclaiming they wished to offer thanks for\nsaving her, and I thought you might come.
So Ieyasu ain't coming to this shindig?

Master Ieyasu has a conference with
members of the Alberian royal family,
and has given me a letter of apology
to deliver in his stead.

Ieyasu sure stays hopping.
Pretty impressive he can still
give chumps the ol' one-two despite
all a' that paper-pushing he does.
I have heard your grandfather managed\na similarly praiseworthy balance of both\npolitical work and martial-arts training.
Say, Sazanka? Can I pull on your coat\nabout my grandpappy and the shogunate?
Turns out I don't know bubkes about the\nwork he did as a vassal of the shogunate,\nor even what went on at the castle.
I only met him a few times, so most of\nwhat I know is second-hand, but...
Your grandfather gained the respect of\na great many generals as a swordmaster\nand instructor to the shogun family.
This connection also lead him to serve as\ninstructor for the leaders of the clans—\nand even Master Ieyasu himself.
Well, I'll be dipped in honey.\nI had no idea.
Still, how did a sword instructor end up\nbeing in charge of an Underworld Key?
It sounds like your grandfather's goal\nwas the impetus for that.
You mean his wantin' to be the\nstrongest swordsman ever?!
Yes. With that in mind, he never idled in\nhis training, even after being given a\ntask as important as teaching a shogun.
That industriousness earned him trust,\nand he was eventually selected to be the\nguardian of an Underworld Key.
Can't believe my grandpappy was\nso dang diligent...

When he first told me they made him
a vassal, I thought it was baloney.
He always did like to yap a big game,
after all.
Looking at you, I can imagine that.
Ha! Well, we are two peas in a pod!
Do you know why he left the shogunate?
I recall something about his saying he was\nleaving in order to protect his family.
I think this was right around the same time\nhe was entrusted with the Underworld Key.
So long as I'm the humdinger in charge\nof this here Underworld Key, me and mine\nain't never gonna be safe.
So what say you hop on the trolley and\nlemme do my duty at their side from this\nday forward, eh?
From what I hear, he originally aspired to\nserve as a vassal of the shogun in order\nto safeguard his family in Hinomoto.
(Everything he did, he did for us...)
(But now he and Momoyo are both pushin'\nup pansies, so what good is all this power\nI've been workin' for...?)
Her family is just over there.
Oh, you're from the Halidom!\nHave you seen our daughter Annie?!
Can't say as we have.\nWhy the worry, toots?
She's gone! She was in the house this\nmorning, but now she's just vanished!
Let's split up and look for her.
(I'm getting a very bad feeling about...\nWait! Over there!)
Heh heh heh. Now that we have the bait,\nall the remains is how to best lay it.

Ho, looks like I fished up an attendant of
the Boar Wyrmclan! But I'm afraid it's
your warrior companion that I'm after.
Bring her to me at once.
But what I CAN do is end your life! Haaah!
Hold on, Annie! I've got you!
You picked a bad moment for playtime,\nmy friends. Haaaaaah!
Listen here, little one: I'm letting you go so\nyou can deliver a very important message.
Well, heck. The sun's already cheesed it,\nand now Sazanka's gone, too.
Hey there, squirt! Good to see you ain't\nfull'a holes! ...Er, but why are you alone?
She saved me, but the bad man\ncame and took her awaaaay!
